class Solution {
    public int removePalindromeSub(String s) {
        if (s.isEmpty()) return 0;
        int left = 0, right = s.length() - 1;
        while (left < right) {
            if (s.charAt(left) != s.charAt(right)) return 2;
            left++;
            right--;
        }
        return 1;
    }
}
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(N)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: The solution checks if the input string is a palindrome. If it is, the function returns 1, as the entire string can be removed in one step. If not, it returns 2, as the string can be divided into two palindromic subsequences ('a's and 'b's). This approach takes advantage of the fact that the string consists only of 'a' and 'b'.
